Deprecated Methods
com.versant.util.DBUtility.addVol(String, String, String)
          As of JVI7.0, replaced by DBUtility.addVol(String,Properties) 
com.versant.util.DBUtility.addVol(String, String, String, String, String, boolean)
          As of JVI7.0, replaced by DBUtility.addVol(String,Properties) 
com.versant.trans.VEnumeration.asHandleArray()
          Returns all the elements as a com.versant.fund.Handle array.

This method is not implemented for cursor based queries. 
com.versant.trans.VEnumeration.nextBatch()
          Return the next batch of objects. The batch of objects returned will be read from all connected databases using group read. The batch size used is 100. The default lockmode is used to group read the objects.

 
com.versant.trans.VEnumeration.nextHandle()
          This method is similar to nextElement() on java.util.Enumeration, but it returns the result as a com.versant.fund.Handle. this method throws java.util.NoSuchElementException if there are no more objects in the VEnumeration to iterate over.
